CLERIC -- Common Lisp Erlang Interface

CLERIC is an implementation of the Erlang distribution protocol, comparable with
erl_interface and jinterface.

Homepage: http://common-lisp.net/project/cleric/


How to install:

The easiest way to install CLERIC is to use ASDF-Install:

  > (asdf-install:install :cleric)

One can also download a tarball from:

  http://common-lisp.net/project/cleric/releases/

To check out the latest code, use git:

  $ git clone http://github.com/flambard/CLERIC.git


Dependencies:

  - usocket
  - MD5
  - IEEE-Floats

These libraries should be downloaded and installed automatically by ASDF-Install.
